---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Max"
  description="About Max, a media computer scientist, API product person, former founder, and Postman team member."
  image="/images/max-about-focus.png"
>
  <section class="about-hero container">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">About Max</p>
      <h1>I build API products where people, data, and systems meet.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        I have a master&apos;s degree in Media Informatics, a long-running love for
        digital products, and a very particular soft spot for APIs. This garden
        is where I collect ideas about technology, product thinking, and the
        systems that quietly make good experiences possible.
      </p>
    </div>
    <figure class="portrait">
      <img
        src="/images/max-about-focus.png"
        alt="Portrait of Max"
        loading="eager"
      />
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section class="story-band">
    <div class="container story-grid">
      <div class="story-intro">
        <p class="eyebrow">The Short Version</p>
        <h2>From media informatics to API ecosystems.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="story-copy">
        <p>
          My path into the digital world started with media informatics. I studied
          in Regensburg and Duesseldorf, earned my bachelor&apos;s and master&apos;s
          degrees, and kept being drawn to the same question: how do we shape
          technology so it becomes useful, understandable, and reliable for real
          people?
        </p>
        <p>
          During my studies, I co-founded icho systems, where we worked on
          products designed to support people living with dementia. That early
          experience still matters to me. It taught me that technology should not
          be impressive for its own sake. It should help, connect, and reduce
          friction where life is already complicated enough.
        </p>
        <p>
          Over the years, APIs became my favorite place to work. I spent several
          years as a Product Owner for APIs, first at
          <a href="http://developer.db.com/">Deutsche Bank</a> and later at
          <a href="https://developer.condor.com/">Condor Airlines</a>. At Condor,
          I helped build a full API platform with an outstanding team, covering
          the data and capabilities behind booking, operations, authentication,
          and many of the moving parts that keep an airline running.
        </p>
        <p>
          I am also a certified Product Owner and certified in Agile Leadership,
          which fits the way I like to work: clear ownership, collaborative
          teams, and enough structure to move complex products forward without
          losing curiosity.
        </p>
        <p>
          Since 2026, I have been working at
          <a href="https://www.postman.com/">Postman</a>, one of the world&apos;s
          leading API tooling companies. It feels like a natural next chapter:
          closer to the craft, the community, and the future of how APIs are
          built, described, shared, and used.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container focus-section" aria-labelledby="focus-title">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">What Drives Me</p>
      <h2 id="focus-title">APIs are more than interfaces.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="focus-grid">
      <article>
        <span>01</span>
        <h3>Product clarity</h3>
        <p>
          I like turning messy needs into usable capabilities, clear contracts,
          and systems that teams can actually build on.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>02</span>
        <h3>Shared understanding</h3>
        <p>
          The best API work happens when product, engineering, operations, and
          business teams can speak about the same thing without translating
          everything twice.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>03</span>
        <h3>Useful technology</h3>
        <p>
          From assistive products to airline systems, I care about tools that make
          complex situations easier to handle.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container closing-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">This Garden</p>
    <blockquote>
      I use this space to think in public, collect notes, and follow the threads
      between product work, APIs, digital systems, and the ideas that keep
      growing after a project is shipped.
    </blockquote>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    display: grid;
    min-height: calc(100vh - 68px);
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(320px, 1fr);
    align-items: center;
    gap: clamp(28px, 5vw, 60px);
    padding-block: 68px 52px;
  }

  h1,
  h2,
  h3 {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
    font-weight: 520;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  h1 {
    max-width: 780px;
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5.55rem);
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.65rem);
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.6vw, 1.85rem);
  }

  .hero-copy {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .hero-copy .lede {
    max-width: 650px;
    margin: 28px 0 0;
  }

  .portrait {
    overflow: hidden;
    margin: 0;
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
  }

  .portrait img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .story-band {
    border-block: 1px solid var(--line);
    background:
      linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(13, 107, 87, 0.1), transparent 36%),
      rgba(255, 253, 248, 0.7);
  }

  .story-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(220px, 0.8fr) minmax(0, 1.2fr);
    gap: clamp(32px, 7vw, 92px);
    padding-block: 78px;
  }

  .story-intro {
    position: sticky;
    top: 102px;
    align-self: start;
  }

  .story-copy {
    color: #34312d;
    font-size: clamp(1.03rem, 1.8vw, 1.18rem);
  }

  .story-copy p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .story-copy p + p {
    margin-top: 1.25em;
  }

  .focus-section {
    padding-block: 76px 64px;
  }

  .section-heading {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(160px, 0.45fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: 28px;
    align-items: end;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }

  .focus-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 18px;
  }

  .focus-grid article {
    min-height: 250px;
    padding: 24px;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: var(--surface);
  }

  .focus-grid span {
    display: inline-flex;
    margin-bottom: 54px;
    color: var(--accent-strong);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 860;
  }

  .focus-grid p {
    margin: 16px 0 0;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .closing-section {
    padding-block: 20px 92px;
  }

  blockquote {
    max-width: 940px;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4.2vw, 3.4rem);
    line-height: 1.08;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .about-hero,
    .story-grid,
    .section-heading,
    .focus-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .about-hero {
      min-height: auto;
      padding-block: 54px 38px;
    }

    .story-intro {
      position: static;
    }

    .story-grid,
    .focus-section {
      padding-block: 54px;
    }

    .focus-grid article {
      min-height: auto;
    }

    .focus-grid span {
      margin-bottom: 30px;
    }
  }
</style>
